The Vice President has issued a statement regarding the new quarterly reports posted on Recovery.gov, which provide more detailed information about the use of funds from the Recovery Act. The reports show that the Recovery Act is continuing to create jobs and support economic growth across the country. Recipients of the funds have reported directly funding over 670,000 jobs in the last quarter, which aligns with independent estimates that the Recovery Act is supporting about 3 million jobs overall. The reports also highlight an increase in infrastructure jobs, reflecting the ongoing activity in infrastructure projects such as highway construction and clean water initiatives. Additionally, the Recovery Act is supporting hundreds of thousands of education jobs across the country. The Vice President emphasizes that the reports are not perfect or complete but provide real-time data directly from the recipients, offering the public an unprecedented view of how the Recovery Act is being utilized.